China is compelling Tibetan herders to settle in towns for development, depriving them of their traditional way of life.
The government cites overgrazing as the reason for erosion and soil loss.
Tibetan communities are being destroyed, leaving residents without a livelihood.
The relocation program aims to combat desert expansion, a significant issue in China.
Soil erosion affects a large portion of Guizhou, threatening farmers' survival.
Efforts to reverse erosion have been successful in some areas, but urbanization and industrialization exacerbate the problem.
Xinjiang is also grappling with soil erosion, exacerbated by human activities and desertification.
